translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 優秀でやる気はある奴らは優遇されるよな、俺達はここで魔物にいずれ殺されるんだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The talented and motivated guys get favored, huh? We're going to be killed by monsters here eventually.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あれ、ランスさんは・・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Huh, where's Rance-san...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いつの間にかランスがいなくなっていた
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Before I noticed, Rance was gone.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: しばらくしてランスが現れる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: After a while, Rance appeared.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 総統閣下、よかったわ、またねーと女の子が立ち去る
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Supreme Commander, I'm glad. See you again—said the girl as she walked away.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: どこかの家に女の子を連れてこんでやっていたらしい
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It seems he had brought a girl into some house.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ん、どこか頭の抜けた子だったが、締まりはよかった。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hmm, she was a bit slow, but well put together.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: よし、次は頭のいい子とやりたいな。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Alright, next I want to be with a smart girl.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 知能試験に合格した子がいるというルールーハンデルとかいう町にいこう
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Let's go to a town called Ruruhandel, where they say some kids have passed an intelligence test.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍司令部　場所は不明　不明の時は地図だけ出して点滅させずに
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Demon Army Headquarters - Location unknown. When unknown, just show the map without blinking.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ゼス方面軍の魔軍司令部　どこにあるかは不明
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Demon Army Headquarters of the Zeth Front — exact location unknown.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: とか書くのでもいいかな
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Maybe it's okay to write it like that.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔物大将軍ツォトンとハニーキングが居た
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The monster general Tsoton and Honey King were there.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ツォトンはハニーキングに下手に出ている、利用しようとしている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Tsoton is acting subserviently to Honey King, trying to use him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ハニー様が我ら魔軍と手を組んで頂き鬼に金棒でございます
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: With Lord Honey joining forces with our Demon Army, it's like a kettle on an iron rod (an unbeatable combination).

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 君から頂いたバニーさんコスプレをした女の子１２人セット、とてもよかった。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The set of twelve girls dressed in bunny costumes you gave me was really great.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いろいろな個性があってサイコーだったよ。今も連れ歩いているよ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They each had different personalities and it was awesome. I still have them with me.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: もともとハニー一族は我々と同じ魔物、一緒に手を組むのが正しい
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Honey clan is originally demon like us; it's right to join hands together.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いや違うよ、おれら亜人間だよ。人間の仲間。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: No, that's not right. We're demi-humans. Allies of humans.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 人間、カラー、ポピンズとかと一緒なのだ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: We're together with humans, Kawara, Popinz, and others.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: はぁ？？　なにいってんのこのバカと思いつつも、ツォトンは会話を続ける
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Huh?? What is this idiot saying? But Tsoton continued the conversation anyway.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: このゼスの地では、魔法が効かないという理由だけで我々ハニーは迫害されてきた
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: In this land of Zeth, the Honey have been persecuted just because magic doesn't work on us.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 人間にはオシオキをしなければと常々思っていたのだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I've always thought that humans need to be punished.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ＞戦闘後
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: > After the battle

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔物軍はランス達に負けて逃げて行った
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The monster army lost to Rance and his group and fled.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: また、町がありますよ。ルールーハンデルの町と分かる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: There's another town. It's understood to be the town of Ruruhandel.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さきほどと違って、普通な人達が多い。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Unlike before, there are many normal people.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 勉強している者が多かった、どうしたのかと聞くと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Many were studying. When asked what was going on,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍に捕まり、いずれ殺されると脅されていた。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They were captured by the Demon Army and threatened that they would be killed eventually.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 知能試験に合格した優秀な者だけがここに集められている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Only the excellent ones who passed the intelligence test have been gathered here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: この周辺の町から集められた
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They were collected from the surrounding towns.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんとなくみんな誇らしい
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Somehow, everyone seems proud.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さらに上級試験を受けて受かると特別扱いをされるそうだぞ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They say if you take and pass an advanced exam, you get special treatment.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍に手を貸すのはなんだが、魔軍も話が分からない連中じゃないようだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It's a bit iffy to help the Demon Army, but they don't seem like unreasonable people.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 協力して一緒に繁栄するのも悪くないかもとか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Maybe cooperating and prospering together isn't so bad.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 中には　いや、これこそ魔軍のしかけた罠だ、俺は騙されないぞ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Some say, no, this is exactly a trap set by the Demon Army. I won't be fooled.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 奴らの思い通りになってやるものか、今はたえ隙をみて倒してやる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I won't let them have their way. I will wait for a chance to defeat them.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 頭のいい、やる気のある連中がいっぱいという感じ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It feels like there are many smart and motivated people here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: そういえばランスは・・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Speaking of which, Rance...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: また、どこかの家で女の子抱いていて、出てきた所。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: He was holding a girl in some house again, just coming out now.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: きぃーーー、女の子怒っている、こんな事して信じられない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Grrr— the girl is angry, she can't believe he did this.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 訴えてやる、ゼス刑法３３条−７、なんかレイプに関する事の法令とか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: She says she'll sue, citing Zeth Penal Code Article 33-7, some law about rape and such.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いって違反しているとランスに文句を言っている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: She's complaining to Rance that he violated it.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: がはははは、俺様には法律より偉い。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hahahaha, I'm above the law.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: どこいっていたんですか、まったく・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Where were you going, seriously...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ランスがエッチしている間に仕入れた情報
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Information gathered while Rance was having sex.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 知能試験に合格した各町の上位２０％がここに集められており
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The top 20% from each town who passed the intelligence test are gathered here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: この中から１週間に１回、上級試験があり３名ほどの合格者が
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: From them, once a week there is an advanced exam, and about three pass.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍司令部につれていかれたそうです。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Those passers are taken to the Demon Army Headquarters.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんでもそこで敵の総大将である魔物大将軍ツォトン様に謁見して
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: There, they get an audience with the enemy’s supreme commander, the demon general Tsoton.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 直々に褒めてもらえるそうだぞとか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Apparently, they are personally praised by him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２日前の試験で合格した者の特徴を聞くと、たぶんウルザさんかと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: When asked about the one who passed the exam two days ago, they say it might be Urza-san.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: おお、やっぱり合格していたか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh, so she did pass after all.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: でもどこに連れていかれたかは分からない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: But no one knows where she was taken.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ウルザさんから連絡があるといっていたが、それもない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They said Urza-san would contact us, but there has been nothing.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: しかたない、もう少しこのあたりをうろうろするか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It can't be helped, let's wander around here a bit more.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: その頃、ハニーキングの陣
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Meanwhile, at Honey King's camp.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 部下達と楽しんでいる、世界征服ごっこをしている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: He is having fun with his subordinates, playing 'world domination'.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 戦争だー、戦争といえば、不幸な女の子が沢山生まれる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: War! Speaking of war, lots of unfortunate girls are born.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 優秀でやる気はある奴らは優遇されるよな、俺達はここで魔物にいずれ殺されるんだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The talented and motivated guys get favored, huh? We're going to be killed by monsters here eventually.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あれ、ランスさんは・・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Huh, where's Rance-san...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いつの間にかランスがいなくなっていた
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Before I noticed, Rance was gone.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: しばらくしてランスが現れる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: After a while, Rance appeared.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 総統閣下、よかったわ、またねーと女の子が立ち去る
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Supreme Commander, I'm glad. See you again—said the girl as she walked away.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: どこかの家に女の子を連れてこんでやっていたらしい
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It seems he had brought a girl into some house.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ん、どこか頭の抜けた子だったが、締まりはよかった。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hmm, she was a bit slow, but well put together.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: よし、次は頭のいい子とやりたいな。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Alright, next I want to be with a smart girl.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 知能試験に合格した子がいるというルールーハンデルとかいう町にいこう
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Let's go to a town called Ruruhandel, where they say some kids have passed an intelligence test.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍司令部　場所は不明　不明の時は地図だけ出して点滅させずに
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Demon Army Headquarters - Location unknown. When unknown, just show the map without blinking.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ゼス方面軍の魔軍司令部　どこにあるかは不明
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Demon Army Headquarters of the Zeth Front — exact location unknown.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: とか書くのでもいいかな
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Maybe it's okay to write it like that.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔物大将軍ツォトンとハニーキングが居た
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The monster general Tsoton and Honey King were there.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ツォトンはハニーキングに下手に出ている、利用しようとしている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Tsoton is acting subserviently to Honey King, trying to use him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ハニー様が我ら魔軍と手を組んで頂き鬼に金棒でございます
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: With Lord Honey joining forces with our Demon Army, it's like a kettle on an iron rod (an unbeatable combination).

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 君から頂いたバニーさんコスプレをした女の子１２人セット、とてもよかった。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The set of twelve girls dressed in bunny costumes you gave me was really great.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いろいろな個性があってサイコーだったよ。今も連れ歩いているよ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They each had different personalities and it was awesome. I still have them with me.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: もともとハニー一族は我々と同じ魔物、一緒に手を組むのが正しい
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Honey clan is originally demon like us; it's right to join hands together.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いや違うよ、おれら亜人間だよ。人間の仲間。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: No, that's not right. We're demi-humans. Allies of humans.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 人間、カラー、ポピンズとかと一緒なのだ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: We're together with humans, Kawara, Popinz, and others.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: はぁ？？　なにいってんのこのバカと思いつつも、ツォトンは会話を続ける
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Huh?? What is this idiot saying? But Tsoton continued the conversation anyway.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: このゼスの地では、魔法が効かないという理由だけで我々ハニーは迫害されてきた
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: In this land of Zeth, the Honey have been persecuted just because magic doesn't work on us.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 人間にはオシオキをしなければと常々思っていたのだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I've always thought that humans need to be punished.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ＞戦闘後
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: > After the battle

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔物軍はランス達に負けて逃げて行った
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The monster army lost to Rance and his group and fled.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: また、町がありますよ。ルールーハンデルの町と分かる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: There's another town. It's understood to be the town of Ruruhandel.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さきほどと違って、普通な人達が多い。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Unlike before, there are many normal people.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 勉強している者が多かった、どうしたのかと聞くと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Many were studying. When asked what was going on,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍に捕まり、いずれ殺されると脅されていた。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They were captured by the Demon Army and threatened that they would be killed eventually.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 知能試験に合格した優秀な者だけがここに集められている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Only the excellent ones who passed the intelligence test have been gathered here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: この周辺の町から集められた
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They were collected from the surrounding towns.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんとなくみんな誇らしい
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Somehow, everyone seems proud.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さらに上級試験を受けて受かると特別扱いをされるそうだぞ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They say if you take and pass an advanced exam, you get special treatment.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍に手を貸すのはなんだが、魔軍も話が分からない連中じゃないようだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It's a bit iffy to help the Demon Army, but they don't seem like unreasonable people.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 協力して一緒に繁栄するのも悪くないかもとか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Maybe cooperating and prospering together isn't so bad.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 中には　いや、これこそ魔軍のしかけた罠だ、俺は騙されないぞ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Some say, no, this is exactly a trap set by the Demon Army. I won't be fooled.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 奴らの思い通りになってやるものか、今はたえ隙をみて倒してやる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I won't let them have their way. I will wait for a chance to defeat them.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 頭のいい、やる気のある連中がいっぱいという感じ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It feels like there are many smart and motivated people here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: そういえばランスは・・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Speaking of which, Rance...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: また、どこかの家で女の子抱いていて、出てきた所。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: He was holding a girl in some house again, just coming out now.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: きぃーーー、女の子怒っている、こんな事して信じられない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Grrr— the girl is angry, she can't believe he did this.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 訴えてやる、ゼス刑法３３条−７、なんかレイプに関する事の法令とか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: She says she'll sue, citing Zeth Penal Code Article 33-7, some law about rape and such.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いって違反しているとランスに文句を言っている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: She's complaining to Rance that he violated it.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: がはははは、俺様には法律より偉い。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hahahaha, I'm above the law.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: どこいっていたんですか、まったく・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Where were you going, seriously...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ランスがエッチしている間に仕入れた情報
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Information gathered while Rance was having sex.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 知能試験に合格した各町の上位２０％がここに集められており
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The top 20% from each town who passed the intelligence test are gathered here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: この中から１週間に１回、上級試験があり３名ほどの合格者が
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: From them, once a week there is an advanced exam, and about three pass.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔軍司令部につれていかれたそうです。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Those passers are taken to the Demon Army Headquarters.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんでもそこで敵の総大将である魔物大将軍ツォトン様に謁見して
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: There, they get an audience with the enemy’s supreme commander, the demon general Tsoton.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 直々に褒めてもらえるそうだぞとか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Apparently, they are personally praised by him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２日前の試験で合格した者の特徴を聞くと、たぶんウルザさんかと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: When asked about the one who passed the exam two days ago, they say it might be Urza-san.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: おお、やっぱり合格していたか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh, so she did pass after all.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: でもどこに連れていかれたかは分からない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: But no one knows where she was taken.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ウルザさんから連絡があるといっていたが、それもない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They said Urza-san would contact us, but there has been nothing.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: しかたない、もう少しこのあたりをうろうろするか
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It can't be helped, let's wander around here a bit more.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: その頃、ハニーキングの陣
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Meanwhile, at Honey King's camp.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 部下達と楽しんでいる、世界征服ごっこをしている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: He is having fun with his subordinates, playing 'world domination'.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 戦争だー、戦争といえば、不幸な女の子が沢山生まれる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: War! Speaking of war, lots of unfortunate girls are born.
